{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"fields":{"description":"# Ticket creation-channel provenance\n\n## Context\n\nAuditors and maintainers can already inspect actor, environment, imported source identifiers, and external bindings, but ticket state does not identify the interface that produced the original CREATE event. That leaves debugging dependent on mutable tags and indirect clues when answering whether a ticket entered through the CLI, MCP server, Python library, Jira reconciler, or NDJSON import.\n\nThe current code has two creation seams. Local surfaces converge on src/rebar/_commands/composer.py:create_core through CLI and library/MCP wrappers, while Jira inbound creation composes CREATE data in src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/apply_inbound_records.py. Existing source_* import provenance in composer.py and reducer/_processors.py is prior art for additive CREATE metadata, but it answers where an imported record came from rather than which local ingress created it.\n\n## Why\n\nCreation channel is a single immutable audit dimension. Recording it on the genesis event gives auditors a direct answer without redefining actor, environment, external ID, assignee, or later mutation provenance. The chosen additive contract fits the event-sourced model, keeps old event logs readable, and avoids unreliable call-stack or tag inference for new writes.\n\n## Architecture Decisions\n\n- Add creation_channel to CREATE data and compiled ticket state with the closed compact vocabulary cli, mcp, python, jira, import, unknown.\n- Every live producer declares its channel at its entry boundary. The shared core carries and validates the declared internal value; it does not inspect the call stack. Direct public Python calls default to python.\n- New writes always record a concrete non-unknown value. Historical records without the field project jira only when all creation-stable signals agree: the ticket ID uses the reconciler-generated jira- prefix and the genesis/restored author and env_id are both reconciler. Those projections also carry creation_channel_inferred: true. Every other historical record projects unknown and omits the marker.\n- The inference marker is present only when true. It is diagnostic metadata, not a security attestation.\n- Import creates a new local ticket through the import channel. Existing source_id, source_created_at, source_author, and source_env continue to describe the source record; an exported source creation_channel is not reused as the new local channel.\n- Compaction preserves creation_channel and creation_channel_inferred inside SNAPSHOT.data.compiled_state. The SNAPSHOT envelope continues to describe the compactor, not the ticket creator. SNAPSHOT-only replay and snapshot rebuild must reproduce the same creation provenance as full-log replay.\n- The public change is additive. Older readers ignore the new CREATE keys; newer readers return unknown for non-Jira legacy records. Back-out is code-only: reverting the readers/writers leaves event logs valid because unknown event-data keys are already forward-compatible.\n- No configuration switch or free-form channel extension is added. A future ingress such as a GitHub reconciler extends the closed vocabulary deliberately.\n\n## Scope\n\nIN:\n- CREATE writer plumbing for CLI, MCP, Python, Jira inbound, and NDJSON import.\n- All CREATE-backed helper flows, including ideas, identities, and session logs, attributed to the interface that invoked them.\n- Reducer projection, public ticket-state/output schemas, typed surfaces, export behavior, and documentation.\n- Conservative Jira-only historical inference with false-positive controls.\n- Compaction, SNAPSHOT-only replay, and snapshot rebuild durability.\n\nOUT:\n- Per-mutation provenance, actor/environment/external-ID redesign, cryptographic proof of channel, stack inspection, retroactive event rewrites, analytics dashboards, creation-channel list filters, subchannels for individual commands, and arbitrary custom strings.\n\n## Decomposition and Sequencing\n\nThree child stories deliver independently testable audit increments in dependency order:\n1. 6fe2-ab22-c231-4a41 — define the contract and expose correct local CLI, MCP, and Python attribution.\n2. e622-a596-3ceb-4f74 — add Jira/import attribution and conservative legacy Jira inference; depends on 6fe2.\n3. 568c-b44b-7e2b-4d87 — prove and preserve recorded, inferred, and unknown values through compaction and SNAPSHOT replay/rebuild; depends on e622.\n\nThe stories share reducer surfaces and therefore run sequentially through depends_on links. This is a multi-story feature and should use a Gerrit feature branch named feature/creation-channel-provenance; each child lands there through both review votes, followed by one gated no-ff merge change to main.\n\n## Risks and Mitigations\n\n- Missed producer path: enumerate every create_core and direct CREATE writer call site and pin each public facade/helper with a behavioral test.\n- False historical attribution: require the exact three-signal Jira predicate and add near-miss negative cases; never infer CLI, MCP, Python, or import.\n- Snapshot data loss: assert the fields inside compiled_state after source CREATE retirement and test rebuild_snapshot_from_full_log separately.\n- Contract drift: define the enum once, validate at writer boundaries, and reference the same vocabulary from the JSON schema and documentation.\n- Compatibility: keep the change additive and optional on stored historical events; no migration or destructive rewrite is performed.\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n- Auditors can distinguish cli, mcp, python, jira, and import creation through existing show/list/export state projections.\n- Historical Jira records are labeled jira with creation_channel_inferred=true only when the deterministic predicate matches; all other legacy records report unknown.\n- Every CREATE-backed ticket/entity helper reports the invoking interface rather than its internal implementation path.\n- Compaction and snapshot rebuild preserve the exact channel and inference marker after original events are retired.\n- The public schema and documentation define the vocabulary, default/fallback semantics, import behavior, and diagnostic trust boundary.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Local ingress attribution is complete: CLI, MCP, and direct Python creation plus their idea/identity/session-log helpers return the expected channel and no new local CREATE reports unknown. Prove with uv run pytest -q tests/interfaces/facades/test_creation_channel.py.\n- [ ] External ingress attribution is complete: Jira inbound reports jira, NDJSON import reports import, the exact legacy Jira predicate reports jira plus creation_channel_inferred=true, and all near-miss legacy cases report unknown without the marker. Prove with uv run pytest -q tests/interfaces/io/test_creation_channel.py tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/mutate/test_creation_channel.py.\n- [ ] Public show/list/export outputs and ticket_state schemas expose only the six documented channel values and the optional true-only inference marker. Prove with uv run pytest -q tests/interfaces/contracts/test_schema_ticket_state.py tests/interfaces/contracts/test_schema_outputs.py tests/interfaces/io/test_export_ndjson.py.\n- [ ] Full-log, compacted SNAPSHOT-only, legacy-SNAPSHOT, and rebuilt-SNAPSHOT replay produce identical recorded/inferred/unknown provenance after folded CREATE events are retired. Prove with uv run pytest -q tests/interfaces/lifecycle/test_creation_channel_compaction.py tests/scripts/reducer/test_reducer_snapshot.py.\n- [ ] The three child stories are closed and their reviewed changes are present in the feature branch merged to main; prove the hierarchy with uv run rebar deps jira-reb-977 and the repository state with git log --oneline --decorate origin/main.\n- [ ] Documentation in docs/event-schema.md and docs/output-schemas.md defines the CREATE/SNAPSHOT placement, enum, inference predicate, import semantics, and distinction from actor/environment/source_* provenance. Prove with uv run pytest -q tests/interfaces/contracts/test_schema_coverage.py and make lint."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784259237810606001,"uuid":"a6be90e3-831a-4daa-a161-5f3b64d965e4"}